<title>SOUTH AFRICA: TABLE - Kelgran yr share rises, no div.</title>
<headline>TABLE - Kelgran yr share rises, no div.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended June 30</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - weighted		34.6	  vs   28.1</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 nil	   vs    9.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   29.61	 vs   20.45</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   32.18	 vs   21.27</p>
<p>    Tax			  1.61	 vs    0.66</p>
<p>    Interest paid	    8.08	 vs    4.99</p>
<p>    Turnover		 403.56	 vs  289.53</p>
<p>    Exceptional items(*)   5.37 loss  vs    nil</p>
<p>Full name: Kelgran Ltd</p>
<p>(*)Following a military coup during May 1997 and the current uncertainty regarding the future political stability in Sierra Leone, Kelgran's full investment in Sierra Leone amounting to 5.4 million rand was written off as an extraordinary item.</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said it expected earnings per share to show reasonable real growth over the 34.6 cents reported for the 1996/97 financial year.</p>
